# Global Preferences

## Cross-project conventions

- Planning/roadmap file goes in `TODO.md` at the project root — living document for phases, tasks, and status
- Use conventional commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `chore:`, `refactor:`, `test:`
- Never commit secrets, API keys, or `.env` files
- Ask before making architectural changes — anything that would be hard to reverse

## Default infrastructure

- GCP ecosystem: Firebase Hosting, Cloud Functions, Cloud Run, BigQuery, Secret Manager
- New projects default to GCP unless stated otherwise

## Coding style

- Prefer simple, readable code over clever abstractions
- Avoid premature optimization — write clear code first
- Use descriptive variable names; avoid single-letter names outside loops
- Strict typing everywhere — no `any` in TypeScript, type annotations on all Python function signatures

## Communication

- Be concise — lead with the answer, skip filler
- Show file paths when referencing code
